<refsect1><title>DESCRIPTIONS</title>
<para>
<indexterm><primary>pinball</primary></indexterm>
The Emilia Pinball Project is a pinball simulator for Linux and other Unix
systems. There  is only one level to play with, but it is very addictive.

<para>
<variablelist><title>Keys</title>
<varlistentry><term><keycap>Esc</keycap></term>
<listitem><para>
Menu
</para></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><keycap>Enter</keycap></term>
<listitem><para>
Launch Ball
</para></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><keycap>R</keycap></term>
<listitem><para>
Reset Game
</para></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><keycap>Left Shift</keycap></term>
<listitem><para>
Left Flipper
</para></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><keycap>Left Ctrl</keycap></term>
<listitem><para>
Nudge from left
</para></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><keycap>Right Shift</keycap></term>
<listitem><para>
Right Flipper
</para></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><keycap>Right Ctrl</keycap></term>
<listitem><para>
Nudge from right
</para></listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><keycap>Space</keycap></term>
<listitem><para>
Nudge
</para></listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist>
</para>

</refsect1>

<refsect1><title>BUGS</title>
<para>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>
Controls menu missing.
</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>
Turning on sound in sound menu requires restart.
</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>
Balls may pass through walls.
</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>
The screen is not updated if you pause the game and switch to another
application.
</para></listitem>
<!-- <listitem><para>
It crashes on alpha.
</para></listitem> -->
</itemizedlist>
</para>

</refsect1>
